Sentencas: In this work the identifiability and estimability of a 17-state nonlinear solid oxide fuel cell model are studied.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: A model is identifiable if the value of each model parameter can be uniquely determined under ideal conditions.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: A model is estimable if each parameter can be determined from a specific experimental design or data set.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The identifiability of the fuel cell model was tested by partitioning the main model into four submodels whose identifiability could be verified.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The estimability of the model was studied using sensitivity analysis.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The model of interest was found to be identifiable in all parameters.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The estimability of parameters was tested by varying the external load as a step and also as a square pulse.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The charge transfer capacitance was found to be inestimable from a step change in the external load for a specific cut-off value, whereas all five parameters are estimable from a square pulse design of the external load input This study forms a basis for experimental studies.
Titulo: Identifiability and estimability study for a dynamic solid oxide fuel cell model
